verbose_text: Relative to the naked case, small D 0.1eV and D 0.4eV are strictly required for GNR-R, decreasing in the order of R = OH, F and H. Owing to these, one can see that, if a certain E g (D) value is devised for a graphene flake, the necessary D will be affected by the edge physicochemical nature associated with the saturation.
evidence: D 0.4eV  are strictly required for GNR-R, decreasing in the order of R = OH
